<title>ITALY: Italy's Genoa sees August CPI at 2.8 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Genoa sees August CPI at 2.8 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>GENOA, Italy 1996-08-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Genoa said its August consumer price index was unchanged month-on-month and 2.8 percent higher year-on-year.</p>
<p>In July, Genoa's inflation rate fell 0.1 percent but rose 2.8 percent respectively.</p>
<p>Genoa is one of 10 Italian cities publishing the inflation data over the next two days.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 2.88 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to July 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.0   (-0.1)    2.8  (2.8)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.6   (-0.1)    4.4  (4.9)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0    (0.2)    4.5  (4.7)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.5   (-1.0)    2.6  (1.6)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.0   (-0.1)    1.8  (2.7)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.0   (-0.3)    3.1  (3.0)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.2    (0.2)    4.8  (4.5)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture    -0.3    (0.0)   -0.6  (0.3)</p>
<p>    Education			   1.2    (0.3)    2.1  (2.1)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.0    (0.0)    1.7  (1.7)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.0   (-0.1)    0.7  (0.9)</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom ++392 66129526</p>
